28 under which if she had been devout, 29 I would have felt those ineffable delights 30 felt before and for a longer breath.

43 A little further on, seven golden trees 44 falsified in appearance the long stretch 45 of the middle that was still between us and them;
46 but when I was made so near to them, 47 that the common object, which deceives the sense, 48 did not lose by distance any of its effect,
